onDismissCancelled().Description: Called when dismissing Keyguard has been cancelled, i.e. when the user cancelled the operation or the bouncer was hidden for some other reason.

onDismissSucceeded().Description: Called when dismissing Keyguard has succeeded and the device is now unlocked.

onDismissError().Description: Called when dismissing Keyguard is currently not feasible, i.e. when Keyguard is not available, not showing or when the activity requesting the Keyguard dismissal isn't showing or isn't showing behind Keyguard.

ClassDesc: Callback passed to @B_android#app#KeyguardManager#requestDismissKeyguard_E@ to notify caller of result.
